'''格温多林·伊丽莎白·布鲁克斯'''（{{lang-en|'''Gwendolyn Elizabeth Brooks'''}}，{{bd|1917年|6月7日|2000年|12月3日|catIdx=B}}）是一位美国诗人和老师。1950年她凭借自己的第二本诗集《Annie Allen》获得[[普利策诗歌奖|普利策诗歌奖]]，成为第一位获得此奖的非洲裔美国女性。

她还获得了很多其他荣誉，1968年获得[[伊利诺伊州|伊利诺伊州]][[桂冠诗人|桂冠诗人]]称号<ref>{{cite web|title=Illinois Poet Laureate|url=http://www.illinois.gov/poetlaureate/Pages/brooks.aspx|accessdate=2015-03-06|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150228221913/http://www.illinois.gov/poetlaureate/Pages/brooks.aspx|archivedate=2015年2月28日}}</ref>，1985年成为国会图书馆桂冠诗人诗歌顾问。<ref>{{cite web | author= | title=Poet Laureate Timeline: 1981–1990 | url=http://www.loc.gov/poetry/laureate-1981-1990.html | publisher=[[Library_of_Congress|Library of Congress]] | year=2008 | accessdate=2008-12-19 | archive-date=2020-05-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200523102744/http://www.loc.gov/poetry/laureate-1981-1990.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Hughes_and_Gwendolyn_Brooks.jpg|thumb]] -->

1917年6月7日格温多林·伊丽莎白·布鲁克斯出生于[[堪萨斯州|堪萨斯州]][[托皮卡|托皮卡]]，2000年12月3日在[[伊利诺伊州|伊利诺伊州]][[芝加哥|芝加哥]]去世。<ref name=nytobit>{{cite news |author=Mel Watkins |coauthors= |title=Gwendolyn Brooks, Whose Poetry Told of Being Black in America, Dies at 83 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2000/12/04/books/gwendolyn-brooks-whose-poetry-told-of-being-black-in-america-dies-at-83.html |quote=Gwendolyn Brooks, who illuminated the black experience in America in poems that spanned most of the 20th century, winning the Pulitzer Prize in 1950, died yesterday at her home in Chicago. She was 83. |newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=2000-12-04 |accessdate=2012-09-13 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308172125/https://www.nytimes.com/2000/12/04/books/gwendolyn-brooks-whose-poetry-told-of-being-black-in-america-dies-at-83.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>她的母亲是一名老师，她后来因为负担不起[[医学院|医学院]]的学费也选择了当老师。家人曾说她的祖父以前是奴隶，在[[南北战争|南北战争]]期间逃脱[[美國奴隸制度|奴役]]加入了联邦军队。<ref>{{cite book |last=Kent |title=A Life of Gwendolyn Brooks |year=1993 |pages=1–2}}</ref>

布鲁克斯六周大时，她的家人在大迁徙期间搬到了芝加哥。从那时起，她一直住在芝加哥。1936年毕业于威尔逊初级学院。在学校的经历影响了她的作品，她的诗经常描写黑人社会中的贫穷、种族不平等和吸毒的现象。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Williams|first1=Kenny Jackson|authorlink1=|editor1-last=Andrews|editor1-first=William L.|editor2-last=Foster|editor2-first=Frances Smith|editor3-last=Harris|editor3-first=Trudier|title=The Concise Oxford Companion to African American Literature|date=2001|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780198031758|page=47|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-9XtCY7cijMC&pg=PA47&dq=gwendolyn+brooks+oxford+companion&hl=en&sa=X&ei=CcH4U8qWN_fNsQTy34LgDw&ved=0CB8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Englewood&f=false|accessdate=2014-08-23|chapter=Brooks, Gwendolyn|archive-date=2019-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829003144/https://books.google.com/books?id=-9XtCY7cijMC&pg=PA47&dq=gwendolyn+brooks+oxford+companion&hl=en&sa=X&ei=CcH4U8qWN_fNsQTy34LgDw&ved=0CB8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Englewood&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>

布鲁克斯幼年时期开始写作，她的母亲鼓励她说“你将成为另一个保罗·劳伦斯·邓巴。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2000/12/05/books/gwendolyn-brooks-83-passionate-poet-dies.html?pagewanted=all|title=New York Times|last=Watkins|first=Mel|date=2000-12-05|work=Gwendolyn Brooks, 83, Passionate Poet, Dies|access-date=2016-03-14|via=|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308141322/https://www.nytimes.com/2000/12/05/books/gwendolyn-brooks-83-passionate-poet-dies.html?pagewanted=all|dead-url=no}}</ref><nowiki></nowiki>

早期的教育经验，使布鲁克斯从不刻意追求四年制学位，因为她知道，她只想成为一名作家。“我不是一个学者，”她后来说，“我只是爱写作并总是去写作。”<ref name="Hawkins">{{cite web|url=http://www.jmu.edu/furiousflower/archives/94hawkins_brooks_intervi.shtml|title=1994 Gwendolyn Brooks Interview|website=James Madison University Furious Flower Poetry Center|ref=JMU|last1=Hawkins|first1=B. Denise|accessdate=2015-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160824235512/http://www.jmu.edu/furiousflower/archives/94hawkins_brooks_intervi.shtml|archive-date=2016-08-24|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

